      "order": 1,
      "Description": "As artificial intelligence becomes more widely used in healthcare settings, understanding who holds responsibility for its outcomes is increasingly important for everyone involved in patient care. This lesson explores the shared accountability that exists between clinicians, healthcare providers, and technology vendors when AI tools are used to support clinical decisions. You will learn how responsibility is distributed across these different roles, and what that means in practice when things go wrong or when AI outputs are unclear. The lesson is designed to be accessible for those who are new to the topic, using straightforward examples drawn from real-world healthcare contexts. By the end, you will have a clearer picture of your own responsibilities and how to work confidently within a system where AI plays a growing role.",
